Hyperliquid Listing Policy Recommendations
This page offers recommendations on listing and delisting policies for the hyperliquid exchange. - stalequant

Methodology
Scoring is based on 100 total points split equally between five measures.
Market cap (20 points)
Low market cap coins are less important, less profitable, and prone to manipulation. This uses the reported CoinGecko market cap and assigns points from 0 for below $1m to 20 for above $5b.
Spot volumes (20 points)
Coins with illiquid spot markets are prone to manipulation, less important, and less profitable. Further, they create issues with oracle stability. We consider both total volume and a geometric mean designed to favor coins with liquid markets on multiple venues. Specifically, the geometric mean is taken over the three most liquid exchanges for each coin on each day (adding $1 for regularity) and averaged to the coin level over the most recent 30 days. To penalize coins with large value drops, volume is dollarized on each day using the lower of that day's low price and the current price. We consider spot pairs with USD or USD-stablecoin quote currencies on Binance, Bybit, Coinbase, Crypto.com, Gate, Kraken, Kucoin, MEXC, and OKX. For each of the two measures, we assign 0 points for below $10k/day and 10 points for above $1b/day.
Futures volumes (20 points)
Coins with illiquid futures markets are less desirable for the same reason coins with illiquid spot markets are undesirable. Calculations are similar to spot volumes, with analysis consisdering only USD and USD-stablecoin based linear futures. We consider futures volumes on Binance, BitMEX, Bybit, Crypto.com, Gate, HTX, Kraken Futures, Kucoin, MEXC, and OKX.
Hyperliquid activity (20 points)
Coins that are not heavily traded on Hyperliquid are of less interest and less desirable. We use average daily volume and average daily open interest over the previous 30 days, assigning 0 points for less than $1k and 10 points for above $100m for each.
Hyperliquid liquidity (20 points)
Coins that have poor market maker support on Hyperliquid are more vulnerable to manipulation. We consider four measures, each scored out of 5. First, we consider the percentage of volume accounted for by the HLP over the past 30 days, assigning 0 points for above 50% and 5 points for 0. Second, we consider the percentage of open interest accounted for by the HLP, assigning 0 points for above 10 percent and 5 points for 0. Third, we consider the average slippage of $3k orders, assigning 0 for more than 5bp and 5 for 0bp. Fourth, we consider the slippage of $30k, assigning 0 for above 50bp and 5 for 0bp.
